# PaddleOCR PP-OCRv5 mobile — third-party redistribution pins (Multi-Model)
#
# These SHA-256 hashes pin the byte-for-byte content of the *dictionary* files
# that are redistributed in this repository under the `paddle` build flavor at
#
#   app/src/paddle/assets/paddleocr/v5/
#
# This file is the third-party / license-side mirror of the asset-internal
# SHA256SUMS file shipped next to the assets themselves
# (`app/src/paddle/assets/paddleocr/v5/SHA256SUMS`). They MUST stay identical
# for the *_dict.txt entries; the asset-internal file is the one consumed by
# the Gradle build (`verifyPaddleAssetSha256`) and at runtime by
# `de.schliweb.makeacopy.utils.ocr.paddle.PaddleAssets`.
#
# Notes
# - Recognition models are now multi-model (8 language-group recognizers +
#   1 detection model). The previous single-rec layout (`rec.ort` /
#   `rec_dict.txt` / fixed V=438) has been removed and is intentionally NOT
#   pinned here anymore.
# - `*.ort` files are intentionally NOT pinned: they are produced by a local
#   reduced-ORT conversion (paddle2onnx → onnxruntime basic-opt) which is not
#   bit-for-bit reproducible across host toolchains. The build verifies their
#   presence and non-empty size only; the dict files are the cryptographic
#   anchor of the redistributed payload.
# - `*.onnx` files are intermediate spike/conversion artifacts and are NEVER
#   shipped as release assets. The Gradle task `failOnPaddleOnnxAssets` and
#   the runtime gate `PaddleAssets.rejectOnnxAssetsOrThrow` enforce this.
#
# Format: `<sha256>  <filename>` — same convention as `sha256sum -c`.

